title: LSU fans cooking whole alligators ahead of big game against...
text:
This is not your typical tailgating fare.
In social media posts that are quickly going viral, LSU fans proudly posted whole alligators being cooked in anticipation of Saturday night’s key matchup against the Florida Gators.
[ Warning: Images may be graphic to some]
>> Read more trending stories
Alligator is on the pit. #LSU #Florida #GameDay pic.twitter.com/Kc4W4anrLc
— Michelle (@Mimo1001) October 17, 2015 @SDS It's game day, y'all. #LSU pic.twitter.com/WAzAeACjJO
— Beerded (@BowlOfOhs) October 17, 2015 What do we eat? Gator meat. @LSUfball See you shortly @brantleysalter #LSU #GeauxTigers #gators #football #sec pic.twitter.com/FU9Km4RQOT
— Rick Greene (@rickgreene23) October 17, 2015 #LSU fans, today is the PERFECT day for tailgating for a Top 10 #SEC matchup at night in Death Valley. Gator cookin! pic.twitter.com/OljRnAB2pS
— Emily Villere Dixon (@emilyvdixon) October 17, 2015 LSU mascot Mike VI also enjoyed alligator-inspired fare, dining on “Gator tartare,” according to his Instagram account.
Gator tartare. How do you like your gator? #lsu #lsufootball
A photo posted by Mike VI, LSU's Live Mascot (@miketigervi) on Oct 16, 2015 at 7:31am PDT
